:Info: dm_set_system_dir:  1985-02-21  dm_set_system_dir

Syntax as a command:  dm_set_system_dir PATH {-ctl_args}


Function:  sets the Data Management per-system directory for the user's
process.  The per-system directory should only be set via this command
if the user is setting up a test DM system, otherwise the default
per-system directory should be used.


Arguments:
PATH
   is the pathname of the directory which is to be used as the DM
   per-system directory.  The default per-system directory is
   ">site>Data_Management".


Control arguments:
-brief, -bf
   suppresses the message about setting the directory as requested.
-long, -lg
   enables the printing of the confirmatory message.  (Default)


